{{neolithic}} {{Distinguish|Gumelniţa-Karanovo culture}} [[File:KaranovoVenus.jpg|thumb|left]] The '''Karanovo culture''' is a [[neolithic Europe|neolithic culture]] (Karanovo I-III ca. 62nd to 55th centuries BC) named for the [[Bulgaria]]n village of {{ill|Karanovo, Sliven Province|lt=Karanovo|bg|Караново (област Сливен)}} (Караново, [[Sliven Province]] {{coord|42|30|41|N|25|54|54|E|}}). The site at Karanovo itself was a hilltop settlement of 18 buildings, housing some 100 inhabitants.[http://w3.cnice.mec.es/eos/MaterialesEducativos/mem2001/huellas/origenes/neolitico/030dondevivian.htm]. This site was inhabited more or less continuously from the early 7th to the early 2nd millennia BC. [[File:P4050100a.jpg|thumb|left|{{ill|Karanovo, Sliven Province|lt=Karanovo|bg|Караново (област Сливен)}} [[stratigraphy]]]] The layers at Karanovo are employed as a chronological system for [[Balkans prehistory]]:
