{{Infobox academic |era = Modern era |image = |caption = Leif Stenberg in 2011 |name = Leif Erik Stenberg |title = Director |birth_date = December 25, 1959 [[Västra Ämtervik]], [[Sweden]] | death_date = |main_interests = [[Islam]] & [[Science]] and discussions within; Contemporary [[Sufism]] |notable_works = [http://www.cmes.lu.se/2009/08/11/the-islamization-of-science/ The Islamization of Science] |influences = [[Jan Hjärpe]], [[Michel Foucault]] |influenced = }} '''Leif Stenberg''' ([[Ph.D]]) is the Director of the [https://www.aku.edu/ismc/Pages/home.aspx Institute for the Study of Muslim Civilisations]<ref>[https://www.aku.edu/ismc/faculty/pages/profile.aspx?ProfileID=32&Name=Leif%20Stenberg ISMC-AKU staff page]</ref> at the [[Aga_Khan_University|Aga Khan University]] (International) in London. He is the former director of the [[Center for Middle Eastern Studies at Lund University]]. Leif Stenberg received his [[B.A]] degree from [[Lund University]] in 1987 and wrote his doctoral thesis on the Islamization of science, supervised by [[Jan Hjärpe]], in 1996. Stenberg's work has been influenced by both [[Jan Hjärpe]] and [[Michel Foucault]], which is apparent in his doctoral thesis, where Foucauldian concepts and definitions are used.<ref name=doctoral>Stenberg, L. (1996). ''The Islamization of Science: Four Muslim Positions Developing an Islamic Modernity''. Coronet Books {{ISBN|91-22-01723-2}} available online at [http://www.cmes.lu.se/2009/08/11/the-islamization-of-science/ the CMES homepage]{{dead link|date=December 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> His interests also include contemporary Sufism, which he has been actively researching since the mid-1990s.<ref>Bornholm Helena ''Mellanöstern i en Samtida Värld'' Tvärsnitt 2009 available [http://www.vr.se/huvudmeny/tvarsnittnr32009/essamellanosterniensamtidavarld.4.227c330c123c73dc58680002602.html online (in Swedish)] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110612160003/http://www.vr.se/huvudmeny/tvarsnittnr32009/essamellanosterniensamtidavarld.4.227c330c123c73dc58680002602.html# |date=2011-06-12 }}</ref>
In 2009 Stenberg criticised the ''Rosengårdsrapporten'' report by security expert [[Magnus Ranstorp]] which contained assertions that there was a growing jihadist movement in the [[Rosengård]] suburb in Malmö as being "full of prejudice" and lacking academic depth. This criticism turned into controversy when it in 2016 turned out that terrorist [[Osama Krayem]] had grown up in the area.<ref name="sr12apr2016">{{cite web|title=Hade Rosengårdsrapporten rätt?|url=http://sverigesradio.se/sida/artikel.aspx?programid=1637&artikel=6409483|website=Sveriges Radio|accessdate=26 December 2016}}</ref>
== Media Appearances ==
Stenberg has both contributed and appeared in several national media-outlets in Sweden such as [[Dagens Nyheter]], [[Svenska Dagbladet]] and [[SR P1|Swedish Radio channel P1]]. Leif Stenberg has been increasingly sought after for comments in wake of the [[Arab Spring]], commenting on the [[Muslim Brotherhood]] in [[Dagens Nyheter]]. He also contributed during the [[Jyllands-Posten Muhammad cartoons controversy]].<ref>Stenberg, L. (2011) ”Risken är liten att Egypten utvecklas till en islamisk stat” ''Dagens Nyheter'' [http://www.dn.se/debatt/risken-ar-liten-att-egypten-utvecklas-till-en-islamisk-stat - link]</ref><ref>Stenberg, L. and Jansson, T. (2006) "Bildförbudet utan stöd i Koranen" ''Svenska Dagbladet'' [http://www.svd.se/kultur/understrecket/bildforbudet-utan-stod-i-koranen_274401.svd - link]</ref> Stenberg has also appeared on live television commenting on the roots and developments of the [[Arab Spring]].<ref>Läget i Egypten, Gomorron Sverige, SVT1, aired February 2, 2011 at 07:15 [http://svtplay.se/v/2316939/gomorron_sverige/laget_i_egypten link] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120311213307/http://svtplay.se/v/2316939/gomorron_sverige/laget_i_egypten |date=2012-03-11 }}</ref><ref>Den nordafrikanska revolten, Gomorron Sverige, SVT1, aired January 28, 2011 at 06.43 [http://svtplay.se/v/2310189/gomorron_sverige/den_nordafrikanska_revolten link] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120311213327/http://svtplay.se/v/2310189/gomorron_sverige/den_nordafrikanska_revolten |date=2012-03-11 }}</ref>
